s in human society throughout times.  aMode of access: Internet via World Wide Web.  aIn English.0 aDescription based on online resource; title from PDF title page (publisher's Web site, viewed 17. Dez 2021) 0aEuropean literatureyRenaissance, 1450-1600xHistory and criticism. 0aLiterature, MedievalxHistory and criticism. 0aSex in literature. 4aFrühe Neuzeit /Kultur. 4aMittelalter /Kultur. 4aSexualität. 7aLITERARY CRITICISM / Medieval.2bisacsh  aArt History.  aEarly-Modern Culture and Literature.  aMedieval Culture and Literature.  aSexuality.  aSocial History.1 aBlaschitz, Gertrud, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aChristoph, Siegfried, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aClason, Christopher R., econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aClassen, Albrecht, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aClassen, Albrecht, eeditor.4edt4http://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/edt1 aCoudert, Allison P., econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aDinzelbacher, Peter, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aFeros Ruys, Juanita, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aFink De Backer, Stephanie, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aGordon, Sarah, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aHahn, Stacey L., econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aHolt, Andrew, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aJost, Jean E., econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aKim, SusanM., econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aKocher, Suzanne, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aLazda Cazers, Rasma, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aLeushui